feat(gov): multisig-gated authority rotation via qsdm/gov/v1 authority-set payload kind

The qsdm/gov/v1 ContractID now carries TWO payload kinds: param-set
(already shipped) and authority-set. Each authority-set tx is one
authority's vote on a (op, address, effective_height) tuple; the
chain accumulates votes and stages the rotation when the M-of-N
threshold is crossed (threshold = max(1, N/2 + 1)). The on-chain
AuthorityList is now itself rotatable without a binary redeploy.

Layers:
- pkg/governance/chainparams/{types,validate,admit,authority,persist}
  - AuthoritySetPayload + AuthorityVoteStore + threshold helper
  - PeekKind dispatch in admit gate
  - Snapshot version bump to 2 (backwards-compatible read of v1)
- pkg/chain/{gov_apply,events}
  - GovApplier dispatches on PayloadKind
  - applyAuthoritySet: vote tally + threshold-cross detection
  - PromotePending now also activates crossed authority proposals,
    mutates authoritySet under authorityMu, drops orphan votes on
    remove, refuses would-empty
  - GovAuthorityEvent family + PublishGovAuthority publisher method
  - 4 new MetricsRecorder methods
- pkg/monitoring/{chain_recorder,gov_metrics}
  - 5 new Prometheus surfaces: voted/crossed/activated counters,
    authority_count gauge, rejected counter
- internal/v2wiring
  - Wires AuthorityVoteStore alongside ParamStore
  - LoadOrNewWith / SaveSnapshotWith for joint persistence
- cmd/qsdmcli/gov_helper
  - propose-authority subcommand
  - inspect now dispatches on wire kind tag

Tests: 50+ new cases across authority store, validate/admit
dispatch, applier rejection branches, persistence round-trip
including v1<->v2 compat, plus an end-to-end integration test
through v2wiring covering a vote -> cross -> activate flow and
a crash-between-cross-and-activate persistence-replay scenario.

Docs: MINING_PROTOCOL_V2.md gains §9.4.7 "Authority rotation" with
wire format, threshold rule, activation semantics, rejection
branches, events, metrics, persistence, CLI. §12.5 of the
deferred-work register marks multisig-gated rotation as SHIPPED.